From: VyOS LS1046A Build <build@vyos-ls1046a-build>
Date: Mon, 26 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] dpaa af_xdp pool attach: DMA-map + BMan seed + RCU publish

0075b-dpaa-af-xdp-pool-attach-bman-seed-rcu

Phase 2 step 2 (spec sec 5.3), depends on 0075a (validation arms + LIODN).

Replaces the final -EOPNOTSUPP in af_xdp_pool_xsk_pool_attach() with the
real implementation that promotes an XSK socket into zero-copy mode:

  Step 2: xsk_pool_dma_map(pool, priv->mac_dev->dev, DMA_ATTR_SKIP_CPU_SYNC)
    On arm64 LS1046A the PAMU is in firmware-programmed bypass; the FMan
    BMI DMAes to physical RAM via the dma-direct path.  DMA_ATTR_SKIP_CPU_SYNC
    omits per-operation cache barriers on the coherent CoreNet fabric.

  Step 3: bman_new_pool() — allocates a dedicated BMan pool ID (BPID) for the
    XSK qband; stores the numeric BPID in priv->xsk_bpid[queue_id] and the
    opaque handle in priv->xsk_bpool[queue_id].

  Step 4: Seed loop — allocates DPAA1_XSK_INITIAL_SEED (8192) buffers in
    batches of 32 from the XSK fill ring via xsk_buff_alloc_batch(); converts
    each XSK DMA address to a struct bm_buffer and releases the batch to the
    new BMan pool via bman_release().  A partial seed (< 4096) sets the
    xsk_bman_seed_short counter; NAPI-hooked refill (patch 0077) will top up.

  Step 5 (xdp_rxq_info_reg_mem_model): Deferred to patch 0077 which has FQ
    context (struct dpaa_fq *) needed for per-FQ mem-model registration.

  Step 6: rcu_assign_pointer(priv->xsk_pool[queue_id], pool) — publishes the
    pool pointer to other CPUs.  From this point the NAPI RX hot-path (patch
    0077's af_xdp_pool_rx_hook) will branch into zero-copy RX for this qband.

Also renames priv->xsk_pamu_win[] (void *, placeholder for the now-removed
PAMU window API) to priv->xsk_bpool[] (struct bman_pool *) in dpaa_eth.h.

BMan API (kernel 6.18.31 mainline): opaque handle-based.
  bman_new_pool() → struct bman_pool * (NULL on OOM)
  bman_free_pool(pool)
  bman_get_bpid(pool) → int
  bman_release(pool, bufs, n)
No bman_alloc_bpid() / bman_free_bpid() exist in mainline.

Build verification (native arm64, linux-6.18.31, aarch64-linux-gnu-):
  make ARCH=arm64 LOCALVERSION=-vyos -j32 \
       drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/af_xdp_pool/
    → CC [M] af_xdp_pool_main.o
    → LD [M] af_xdp_pool.o
  zero errors, zero warnings.

  nm af_xdp_pool.o | grep 'U ':
    U bman_get_bpid   (new — BMan BPID accessor)
    U bman_new_pool   (new — BMan pool allocation)
    U bman_release    (new — BMan buffer release)
    U xp_alloc_batch  (new — behind xsk_buff_alloc_batch() inline)
    U xp_dma_map      (new — behind xsk_pool_dma_map() inline)
    U xp_dma_unmap    (new — behind xsk_pool_dma_unmap() inline)
    U fman_port_get_liodn (from 0075a — validation retained)
    U dpaa_register_flavor_ops / dpaa_unregister_flavor_ops (M0 ABI)
    U __napi_schedule_irqoff / napi_schedule_prep (from 0074)

  All new U-refs are EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL from soc/fsl/bman.c (in-tree,
  always-built on arm64 DPAA1 configs via CONFIG_FSL_BMAN=y).

